# 1. What is a Lambda Expression?

A **Lambda Expression** is a **short way of writing the implementation of a method** for a **functional interface**.

Think of it like this:

Before Java 8:

```java
interface Greeting {
    void greet();
}

class GreetingImpl implements Greeting {

    @Override
    public void greet() {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}

public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Greeting g = new GreetingImpl();
        g.greet();

    }

}
```

There are many things to write:

* Interface
* Class
* Override
* Object creation

Even though the actual work is only:

```java
System.out.println("Hello");
```

---

Java 8 says:

> "Why write all this extra code?"

Instead write:

```java
Greeting g = () -> System.out.println("Hello");
```

Done!

---

# What exactly is happening?

This line

```java
Greeting g = () -> System.out.println("Hello");
```

means

> "Create an object of Greeting and implement its only abstract method using this code."

---

# 2. Why was Lambda Introduced?

Java is an **Object-Oriented Language**.

Everything required classes and objects.

Suppose you wanted to sort employees.

Before Java 8:

```java
Collections.sort(list, new Comparator<Employee>() {

    @Override
    public int compare(Employee e1, Employee e2) {
        return e1.getSalary() - e2.getSalary();
    }

});
```

Lots of unnecessary code.

---

Java 8

```java
Collections.sort(list,
    (e1, e2) -> e1.getSalary() - e2.getSalary());
```

Same work.

Much smaller code.

---

# Problem Before Java 8

Suppose you wanted to print numbers.

Old Java:

```java
class Printer {

    void print(int x) {
        System.out.println(x);
    }

}
```

Need:

* Class
* Method
* Object

Just to print.

Java 8 tries to reduce unnecessary code.

---

# 3. What is Functional Programming?

Before understanding Lambda, understand this concept.

There are two programming styles.

## Object-Oriented Programming

Everything revolves around:

```
Class

↓

Object

↓

Method
```

Example

```java
Car car = new Car();

car.start();
```

---

## Functional Programming

Everything revolves around:

```
Function

↓

Pass Function

↓

Execute Function
```

Instead of passing objects...

You pass behavior.

Example

Instead of saying

```
Use this Printer object
```

You say

```
Use this print logic.
```

That print logic is the Lambda.

