    int add(int a, int b);

}
```

Lambda

```java
Calculator c = (a, b) -> a + b;
```

Many beginners think

```
Where is the class?
```

Good question.

---

Java compiler generates an implementation behind the scenes.

Imagine Java creates

```java
class TempCalculator implements Calculator {

    @Override
    public int add(int a, int b) {

        return a + b;

    }

}
```

Then

```java
Calculator c = new TempCalculator();
```

You don't see this generated class, but conceptually this is what happens.

